 ('406', '450', 'en_us', 'The Arnold Schwartz Memorial Organ', NULL, 'The Arnold Schwartz Memorial Organ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>This beautiful organ, named in memory of the major donor, Mrs. Marie Schwartzs late husband, is Opus 92 of C. B. Fisk, Inc.&nbsp;Church of the Transfiguration has an extensive music program including a Men and Boys Choir and a Girls Choir. Our Music Director, Dr. Claudia Dumschat auditions children from all over the city. Those accepted for the choirs receive an excellent musical education and ample opportunities to perform.</p><p></p>', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-23 12:03:04', '2017-09-25 10:02:02', '34a912e5-f65c-4765-bac2-09a8d59499a3'),
 ('407', '451', 'en_us', 'The St. Joseph of Arimathea Chapel', NULL, 'The St. Joseph of Arimathea Chapel', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The ceiling is decorated with renderings of Fra Angelicos <i>Glory in Paradise</i> and <i>The Last Judgment</i>, painted on canvas panels which have been fitted between the ribs of the plaster vault.&nbsp; Also on view in this chapel is a large painted glass rendering of Raphaels <i>The </i>T<i>ransfiguration</i>. The entrance to the chapel is graced by polychromed wood carvings of the four Archangels, Uriel, Gabriel, Michael and Raphael.</p><p></p>', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-23 12:11:29', '2017-09-23 12:11:29', '462db9f7-336c-4c2f-94db-f0a4d8fc46bd'),
 ('408', '452', 'en_us', 'Singing Boy and Compline Psalms', NULL, 'The Singing Boy and the Compline Psalms', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>This beautiful statue dates from 1871 and is the work of Franklin Simmons, an American sculptor living in Rome. He seems right at home among the <strong>Compline</strong> <strong>Psalms</strong>. (Compline psalms are prayers said at the end of the day.) Fr. George Hendric Houghton, the founding rector, married a drawing teacher, Caroline Graves Anthon, who painted the psalms on parchment. After her death, Fr. Houghton had her paintings executed in glass as a memorial to her.</p>', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-23 12:12:41', '2017-10-01 12:24:10', '8fe4d172-d88d-47e1-bb1a-c6248396704a'),
