 ('181', '455', '10', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Baptisms\",\"slug\":\"baptisms\",\"postDate\":1506174608,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":\"\",\"11\":[\"420\"],\"12\":\"<p>Pulvinar faucibus a dignissim enim accumsan arcu est nunc scelerisque parturient fringilla at vel a adipiscing id dignissim scelerisque. Nascetur mi odio a sit dis consectetur cum donec est adipiscing phasellus risus amet ultrices dis interdum. Montes dictum suspendisse consectetur vestibulum volutpat ridiculus dis nullam ac blandit tellus eu nisl lorem.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-23 13:50:08', '2017-09-23 13:50:08', 'bdfbcc35-820b-4622-a6cb-df5858743c06'),
 ('182', '455', '10', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Baptisms\",\"slug\":\"baptisms\",\"postDate\":1506174600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h3>Planning Holy Baptism<\\/h3><p>From time to time people ask about the requirements for Baptism. The only requirements to begin planning for a Baptism at Transfiguration are:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>A sincere desire to become a Christian or raise your child as a Christian.<\\/li><li>A readiness to begin (or continue) active participation in the life of the \\\"Little Church Around the Corner\\\".<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>If you are sure about both of those requirements, wonderful! It will be a delight to have you with us. The first step to planning a baptism at Transfiguration is to contact the office at 212-684-6770 and speak with the Rector of the church.<\\/p><p>If you are sure about the first requirement but not clear about the second, then we invite you to worship with us at the Church of the Transfiguration on a Sunday and meet us at the coffee hour immediately following the 11:00 am service.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Feel free to introduce yourself to the clergy, attend any of our adult education classes, or investigate our new series of Sunday Eucharistic liturgies at 11:00 am. Geared more for the needs of children and young families: \\u201cshorter and brighter\\u201d with a children\\u2019s address in place of the sermon, and featuring the Girls and Cherub Choirs. In so doing, you\'ll confirm Transfiguration is the right church home for you.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>May God bless you as you contemplate Holy Baptism for yourself or your child.<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"420\"],\"12\":\"<p>We are pleased that you are interested in Holy Baptism at the Church of the Transfiguration. You will find here an intimate, loving, and supportive family of Christians who will do all in their power to encourage you in your life in Christ.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-23 13:59:55', '2017-09-23 13:59:55', 'ccbdd2c1-913d-4ac7-a1a7-c90766bc3448'),
 ('183', '455', '10', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Baptisms\",\"slug\":\"baptisms\",\"postDate\":1506174600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"456\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h3>Planning Holy Baptism<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>From time to time people ask about the requirements for Baptism. The only requirements to begin planning for a Baptism at Transfiguration are:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>A sincere desire to become a Christian or raise your child as a Christian.<\\/li><li>A readiness to begin (or continue) active participation in the life of the \\\"Little Church Around the Corner\\\".<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>If you are sure about both of those requirements, wonderful! It will be a delight to have you with us. The first step to planning a baptism at Transfiguration is to contact the office at 212-684-6770 and speak with the Rector of the church.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>If you are sure about the first requirement but not clear about the second, then we invite you to worship with us at the Church of the Transfiguration on a Sunday and meet us at the coffee hour immediately following the 11:00 am service.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Feel free to introduce yourself to the clergy, attend any of our adult education classes, or investigate our new series of Sunday Eucharistic liturgies at 11:00 am. Geared more for the needs of children and young families: \\u201cshorter and brighter\\u201d with a children\\u2019s address in place of the sermon, and featuring the Girls and Cherub Choirs. In so doing, you\'ll confirm Transfiguration is the right church home for you.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>May God bless you as you contemplate Holy Baptism for yourself or your child.<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"420\"],\"12\":\"<p>Interested in Holy Baptism at the Church of the Transfiguration? You will find here an intimate, loving, and supportive family of Christians who will do all in their power to encourage you in your life in Christ.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-23 14:00:42', '2017-09-23 14:00:42', '280083f0-d399-46a5-a671-88dd762427f9'),
 ('184', '363', '10', '1', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Weddings\",\"slug\":\"weddings\",\"postDate\":1505423640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"364\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Weddings at Transfiguration<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>How Transfiguration became famous as a place to exchange vows remains something of a mystery, but it is generally attributed to the overall openness of the church to people from different Christian denominations, personal situations and backgrounds. Every Saturday in&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.nytimes.com\\/interactive\\/projects\\/cp\\/weddings\\/165-years-of-wedding-announcements\\/world-war-two-weddings\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noreferrer noopener\\\">the 1930s and 40s<\\/a>&mdash;and often on weekdays&mdash;couples would gather in the garden, awaiting their turn to be married in the Holy Family Chapel. The Rector in that era would marry as many as seven couples a day.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We hear from those couples to this day as part of our&nbsp;<em>Little Family<\\/em>&nbsp;community.&nbsp;We send out several newsletters to them each year and a card goes to all those married here on their anniversaries.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>The Space<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Tucked behind a lovely English garden with a fountain, Transfiguration is a neo-Gothic church rich with architectural detail. There are two spaces in which you may choose to be married:<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>The Holy Family Chapel<\\/strong> is a quaint room panelled with dark wood that seats up to 50 people&mdash;is appropriate for smaller weddings. The altar piece is a painted depiction of the betrothal of Mary and Joseph. It is in the Holy Family Chapel that thousands of couples in the post-war years became married, making the Little Church famous for weddings.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><em>I would like to include some images here, so can fill this out further, tomorrow, Mary Jane. We can also include downloads to the newsletters, as it is on the existing wedding page.<\\/em><\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"362\"],\"12\":\"<p>Congratulations on your engagement, and thanks for your interest in becoming married at The Church of the Transfiguration. Our church is a beautiful place with a century-old reputation for marrying couples from all over the world. At one time, Transfiguration solemnized more marriages than any other church! We welcome you to join our \\\"little family\\\", and we hope to become a part of yours.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"Jesse Anders \\/On Point Images \"}}', '2017-09-23 14:08:19', '2017-09-23 14:08:19', '6d23a006-b85a-405e-ac87-2e58b24ac9e9'),
