rivative for \\u201cfour leaves\\u201d) shape consists of four partially overlapping circles of the same diameter. This symbol often represents the four physical elements (earth, water air and fire) and the four cardinal directions (north, south, east and west). In religious settings, the Quatrefoil symbolizes the four Gospels \\u2013 Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John \\u2013 which overlap one another partially but not entirely. In general, this shape represents inclusivity and can also be found prominently as a stained glass window over the Church\\u2019s entryway (see below).<\\/p>\"}},\"642\":{\"type\":\"figure\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"613\"],\"altAttribute\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"credit\":\"\",\"enlarge\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"horizontal\"}},\"643\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>The Triangle is often used in Christianity as a symbol for the Holy Trinity \\u2013 Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. A triangle pointing up demonstrates a strong foundation and sense of stability. The triangle \\u2013 in fact, a green triangle \\u2013 adorns the Rectory entryway (see below) with the inscription of Transfiguration\\u2019s mission Fides Opera (\\u201cFaith in Action\\u201d)*. The logo triangle also resembles one of Transfiguration\\u2019s most noted structural components, the lychgate.<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"609\"],\"26\":\"Gary Norcross\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-01 11:38:05', '2017-10-01 11:38:05', '47c9469f-0022-49e7-92d2-2387823c1704'),
