 ('274', '671', '9', '654', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"654\",\"title\":\"\\u201cI\\u2019m Happy!\\u201d Says the Weeping Cherry Tree\",\"slug\":\"im-happy-says-the-weeping-cherry-tree\",\"postDate\":1507299000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"28\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Yesterday, a weeping cherry tree\\r\\nwas planted in Church of the Transfiguration\\u2019s garden and dedicated to the\\r\\nmemory of my brother, Mark Joseph.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"figure\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"668\"],\"altAttribute\":\"\",\"caption\":\"<p>Fr . van Dooren, Ray Vento, and friends at the tree blessing.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"credit\":\"\",\"enlarge\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"horizontal\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>While I awaited the tree to be blessed, I reached to touch a leaf. The soft green blade filled me with Mark\\u2019s presence. Besides me was a group of friends to share in Father John David\\u2019s blessing of the new addition to the church\\u2019s garden. As we listened to Father\\u2019s prayer, a shaft of sunlight made it\\u2019s way through the surrounding buildings illuminating the young sapling. In the brilliance of God\\u2019s blessing for this autumn morning, I could see my brother\\u2019s smile.<\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Mark was my youngest brother. Born with a learning disability, Mark&nbsp;met life struggles with remarkable courage even unto his death.&nbsp;Those who knew Mark, fell under his spell. He was funny,&nbsp;sometimes cunning, always affectionate, and never forgot anything.&nbsp;He could be introverted, but he could also be the commander-inchief&nbsp;of any gathering. His laughter was infectious. His love for&nbsp;others was sincere and true. It was rare for Mark not to say: \\u201cI\\u2019m&nbsp;happy!\\\"&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"new7\":{\"type\":\"figure\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"669\"],\"altAttribute\":\"\",\"caption\":\"<p>Mark and Ray celebrating Christmas.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"credit\":\"\",\"enlarge\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"horizontal\"}},\"new6\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Mark knew every holiday, but Christmas was the one he waited&nbsp;for all year long. Many years long ago, our mother began the&nbsp;tradition that after Thanksgiving, a small artificial Christmas tree&nbsp;would be set-up in Mark\\u2019s bedroom. Every Christmas that I was&nbsp;visiting my family, I can remember passing by my brother\\u2019s&nbsp;<br>bedroom (usually on purpose to tease him) and see him with&nbsp;wide eyes, head turned toward his tree and looking at every&nbsp;ornament as a king would look out at his kingdom. Of course,all of this was just a prelude to the big event, coming on&nbsp;Christmas morning. From a living room chair, Mark would eye&nbsp;all the wrapped packages looking for one in particular. That one&nbsp;gift that he knew would be there was in a small wrapped box.Gleefully smiling with much anticipation, the removed wrapping&nbsp;would reveal another treasured watch. For Mark, like the pot of&nbsp;gold at the end of a rainbow, a new watch was the big and best&nbsp;prize that he had waited for. \\u201cOh boy!\\u201d he would say holding his&nbsp;new watch amidst discarded wrapping paper and ribbons. It was&nbsp;hard for Christmas lights and glass ornaments to compete with Mark\\u2019s brilliant and&nbsp;joyful expression.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>I have so many wonderful and happy memories of Mark. Now, I await spring when the weeping cherry will be filled with tiny blossoms when I can again see Mark\\u2019s smile and hear his voice say: \\u201cI\\u2019m happy!\\u201d<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"667\"],\"26\":\"Ray Vento\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-06 14:12:23', '2017-10-06 14:12:23', '059e75b9-27b8-4bbb-8de3-b2795852eebb'),
